      "updated": 1767869365568,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Question in interview -> lets say there is a service that creates 1000 req/sec and this service is in our control but there is \na third party service that only supports 10 req/sec, How will third party service will manage stuff?\n\n\nif the third party is not able to scale upto 1000 req/sec then there are only 2 possible options\n1. Only process 10 and then start discarding remaining req\n2. Or it can park the requests. park means it will say you are sending 1000 req/sec  I will process everything but I will not give\nyou the response immediately I will give the response based on my own load capacity, it will take time but you will get your answers\n\nSo when there is a producer that produces lot of data and there is a consumere which can't consume that amount of data due to \nany reason, parking the request is a good way and for parking our request we can use any Message broker system",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Question in interview -> lets say there is a service that creates 1000 req/sec and this service is in our control but there is \na third party service that only supports 10 req/sec, How will third party service will manage stuff?\n\n\nif the third party is not able to scale upto 1000 req/sec then there are only 2 possible options\n1. Only process 10 and then start discarding remaining req\n2. Or it can park the requests. park means it will say you are sending 1000 req/sec  I will process everything but I will not give\nyou the response immediately I will give the response based on my own load capacity, it will take time but you will get your answers\n\nSo when there is a producer that produces lot of data and there is a consumere which can't consume that amount of data due to \nany reason, parking the request is a good way and for parking our request we can use any Message broker system",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
