    {
      "id": "IqYQxwiCh0wXMZja9foft",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1850.0801955004877,
      "y": -17051.44287825838,
      "width": 823.355712890625,
      "height": 450,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#2f9e44",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b6J",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1312661475,
      "version": 432,
      "versionNonce": 1565181251,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1767870809848,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "we have multiple modules for which \nwe have code written and we have put all\nthese modules in one place and run that as\na single unit of server\nthat is called as Monolyth Architecture\nEverything: Frontend Backed & DB running as \n a single system in a single server\n\nAll of the logic stays together and run\ntogether.",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "we have multiple modules for which \nwe have code written and we have put all\nthese modules in one place and run that as\na single unit of server\nthat is called as Monolyth Architecture\nEverything: Frontend Backed & DB running as \n a single system in a single server\n\nAll of the logic stays together and run\ntogether.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "gDfRtP-fyQ0rl38uS0rMj",
      "type": "rectangle",
      "x": 1258.6117771643926,
      "y": -17174.32461645106,
      "width": 0.2518567857173366,
      "height": 0.25185678571870085,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#2f9e44",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b6K",
      "roundness": {
        "type": 3
      },
      "seed": 823562371,
      "version": 3,
      "versionNonce": 731824013,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1767870843510,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false
    },
    {
      "id": "-2tZ8Z67RhLxUO5nLNuRy",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 310.7336924876464,
      "y": -16240.316341864716,
      "width": 2666.626953125,
      "height": 1485,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#2f9e44",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b6L",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 494705261,
      "version": 3118,
      "versionNonce": 1209221101,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1767872811193,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "In a Monolyth Architecture all the different business modules stay together as a singld unit of project. They run as a single server\nand if we have to scale up/down, we scale up/down the complete project\n- Can't scale a dedicated module\n- can't choose diff diff language for different code parts\n- They can become unmanagable if the projects becomes so big like Flipkart(having Flights, grocery, Ecommerce) because same change in payment \n    also need deplyment, submission also need deployment so conflicts will come who will deploy first may be payment system has some bug but they\n    deployed the complete project and because of that everything is now failing\n\nSo there are lot of issues in Monolyth but it is good also in some scenario\nLike Our Application is not that complex like StackOverFlow -> Basic Discussion Forum -> Question, Answers, Comments, Tags not added \n multiple features with time like Flipkart added crazy feature like flipkart flights\nStackOverflow still work as a Monolyth project -> codebase is big but not as big in that we have problem to manage single codebase\n\nLike we are working on our personal project having Monolyth absolutely Ok but when we are working on production, or scale or our business\ngrows like crazy then problem starts\n\nBefore 7-8 years Back leetcode was only problem submission plateform Now a days it is so much more\n1 we can read articles\n2 discussion forum\n3 Video lecture\n4 Interview\n\nSo when our business grows our code module also grows because they might be dependent on old codebase or might not in those cases Monolyth \nbecomes unmanagable.\n\nGoogle(Google 3) manage the code on one repo as Monolyth, Conside Google as an exception as they manage their code\nthey have single repo still the entire development that is setup in Google is way way different than the normal development architecture\nthat we see, for example we go to any company there is a highly likely chance we have to clone the project, In google we dont clone the project\nin our local machine all the project coding is done on the cloud, we directly code using browser, so even having the humoungous amount of code\nBillion line of code is not matter due to it is handled on the cloud and that also not put lot of load due to they work on snapshot based architecture\nthat the code pointer that we are going to change only that much change is going to our cloud machine so they have managed everything very well.\nDeployment also in google is handled differently inside google3 lot of repos that can deploy independently.\nthey dont use Git , they have their own in House version control system as well",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "In a Monolyth Architecture all the different business modules stay together as a singld unit of project. They run as a single server\nand if we have to scale up/down, we scale up/down the complete project\n- Can't scale a dedicated module\n- can't choose diff diff language for different code parts\n- They can become unmanagable if the projects becomes so big like Flipkart(having Flights, grocery, Ecommerce) because same change in payment \n    also need deplyment, submission also need deployment so conflicts will come who will deploy first may be payment system has some bug but they\n    deployed the complete project and because of that everything is now failing\n\nSo there are lot of issues in Monolyth but it is good also in some scenario\nLike Our Application is not that complex like StackOverFlow -> Basic Discussion Forum -> Question, Answers, Comments, Tags not added \n multiple features with time like Flipkart added crazy feature like flipkart flights\nStackOverflow still work as a Monolyth project -> codebase is big but not as big in that we have problem to manage single codebase\n\nLike we are working on our personal project having Monolyth absolutely Ok but when we are working on production, or scale or our business\ngrows like crazy then problem starts\n\nBefore 7-8 years Back leetcode was only problem submission plateform Now a days it is so much more\n1 we can read articles\n2 discussion forum\n3 Video lecture\n4 Interview\n\nSo when our business grows our code module also grows because they might be dependent on old codebase or might not in those cases Monolyth \nbecomes unmanagable.\n\nGoogle(Google 3) manage the code on one repo as Monolyth, Conside Google as an exception as they manage their code\nthey have single repo still the entire development that is setup in Google is way way different than the normal development architecture\nthat we see, for example we go to any company there is a highly likely chance we have to clone the project, In google we dont clone the project\nin our local machine all the project coding is done on the cloud, we directly code using browser, so even having the humoungous amount of code\nBillion line of code is not matter due to it is handled on the cloud and that also not put lot of load due to they work on snapshot based architecture\nthat the code pointer that we are going to change only that much change is going to our cloud machine so they have managed everything very well.\nDeployment also in google is handled differently inside google3 lot of repos that can deploy independently.\nthey dont use Git , they have their own in House version control system as well",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "jVOLkaHsI-VWJTzN-_iR5",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 315.5655835905158,
      "y": -14662.22167154615,
      "width": 2713.138916015625,
      "height": 90,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffffff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b6M",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1849779469,
      "version": 345,
      "versionNonce": 1021456141,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1767872638102,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "MonoRepo -> It is a single repository  containing multiple distinct projects with well defined relationships and this is actually what google uses to manage\n    their dependency the build system that google uses is Bazel which is very efficient vey fast made by Google only.",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "MonoRepo -> It is a single repository  containing multiple distinct projects with well defined relationships and this is actually what google uses to manage\n    their dependency the build system that google uses is Bazel which is very efficient vey fast made by Google only.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
