      "text": "In Normal cycle client send some request and server gives response that is kind of a poll but in websocket nobody has to poll anybody if client want to send\nthe data they can just send that if client doesn't want to send the data, if the server want to send the data to the client they can just send that if both\nof them want to send the data they can even send the data to each other, its a real time system two way communication like chats\n\nchat engine -> we dont need to refresh whatsapp again and again in order to get our latest data hence websockets are for real time communication in a bi-directional\nway(full duplex), the best part is websockets are also based on top of TCP connectoin that measn reliable connection, we can send the data in text form or in binary form or\nany form that we want to send\n\nWebsocket Use Cases\n1. Live location of our driver can be done by websocket\n2. Chatting\nany type of real time communication that we want that can be done by websocket where 2 or more machine and anybody can send to anybody\n\nWebsockets and SSE both of them are good way to solve the problem of giving data back to the client compared to polling\n\nProblem with Websocket -> There can be limit to number of socket connection that we can prepare -> A server can handle 65536 web socket connection per IP\naddress in the theory so SSE can be a better solution here \n\nQ Where Polling is good, what are the use cases for polling? 50:00",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "In Normal cycle client send some request and server gives response that is kind of a poll but in websocket nobody has to poll anybody if client want to send\nthe data they can just send that if client doesn't want to send the data, if the server want to send the data to the client they can just send that if both\nof them want to send the data they can even send the data to each other, its a real time system two way communication like chats\n\nchat engine -> we dont need to refresh whatsapp again and again in order to get our latest data hence websockets are for real time communication in a bi-directional\nway(full duplex), the best part is websockets are also based on top of TCP connectoin that measn reliable connection, we can send the data in text form or in binary form or\nany form that we want to send\n\nWebsocket Use Cases\n1. Live location of our driver can be done by websocket\n2. Chatting\nany type of real time communication that we want that can be done by websocket where 2 or more machine and anybody can send to anybody\n\nWebsockets and SSE both of them are good way to solve the problem of giving data back to the client compared to polling\n\nProblem with Websocket -> There can be limit to number of socket connection that we can prepare -> A server can handle 65536 web socket connection per IP\naddress in the theory so SSE can be a better solution here \n\nQ Where Polling is good, what are the use cases for polling? 50:00",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
