    },
    {
      "id": "pnI_jhYevfPid_Gf8s9sY",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 297.5890224420616,
      "y": -7601.00989948399,
      "width": 2036.7354736328125,
      "height": 1620,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#ced4da",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b8n",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2050970782,
      "version": 3011,
      "versionNonce": 624864755,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1768404342828,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Webhook -> \nSomebody comes to our application and they click on signin with facebook they are immediately \nredirected back to the facebook UI, they are out of our App, assume they successfully loged in to \nfacebook, the moment they successfully loged in to facebook, they how do I know it user is loged in \nsuccessfully or not?\nSo facebook need some mechanism so that facebook can tell us that hey this particular user has requested\nto all of this and he is successfullly loged in so facebook needs an endpoint from our side that facebook\ncan call and tell this is the response from the login attempt its success not do whatever you want\n\nNow think about that there are 1 million or so many startups which will be using facebook login, facebook\nhas that same response object now user is coming from which particular app, facebook can't configure\nseparately there application for login for every particular startup, they have a generic response and who\never want to implement facebook login, facebook says that ok, you want to use facebook login these are \nsome apis that you can hit and please tell me your webhook URL. This will be the URL that I will call to send\nthe data about a login requst this is what webhook is.\n\nSimilar thing in payment gateway -> Razorpay -> redirec to razorpay page -> payment complemented -> razorpary tell\nus using webhook url payment is success or not\n\nHence Webhook is some URL , that means we need to expose some api to it that somebody else like\nrazorpay will call and I will consume the object from razorpay and implement my logic\n\nSo lot of time people call it as a redirect URL or a webhook URL this is like webhook basically means\n\nA webhook is an HTTP request, triggered by an event in a source system(Facebook, Razorpay) and sent to\na destination system(like our app or any other startup).\n\n\nCan we Use Webhook  here -> No because who has the data our backend service our client is a webclient can't\nexpose a webhook but there is a usecase where webhookds can be helpful, when my client is not a webclient.\nWhen may be I am not Leetcode but I am somebody like spoj(Sphere online judge), So Spoj is like Leetcode as\nservice, whay spoj says that hey you want to make Leetcode dont put all of architecture in place I have all this\narchitecture in place already with me, you just register with me and send me your submissions that is coming from\nusers tell me where your testcases are and I will run it on my machine you just pay me,\n\nMight be it changed but for bigger ammount of time Codechef use Spoj.",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Webhook -> \nSomebody comes to our application and they click on signin with facebook they are immediately \nredirected back to the facebook UI, they are out of our App, assume they successfully loged in to \nfacebook, the moment they successfully loged in to facebook, they how do I know it user is loged in \nsuccessfully or not?\nSo facebook need some mechanism so that facebook can tell us that hey this particular user has requested\nto all of this and he is successfullly loged in so facebook needs an endpoint from our side that facebook\ncan call and tell this is the response from the login attempt its success not do whatever you want\n\nNow think about that there are 1 million or so many startups which will be using facebook login, facebook\nhas that same response object now user is coming from which particular app, facebook can't configure\nseparately there application for login for every particular startup, they have a generic response and who\never want to implement facebook login, facebook says that ok, you want to use facebook login these are \nsome apis that you can hit and please tell me your webhook URL. This will be the URL that I will call to send\nthe data about a login requst this is what webhook is.\n\nSimilar thing in payment gateway -> Razorpay -> redirec to razorpay page -> payment complemented -> razorpary tell\nus using webhook url payment is success or not\n\nHence Webhook is some URL , that means we need to expose some api to it that somebody else like\nrazorpay will call and I will consume the object from razorpay and implement my logic\n\nSo lot of time people call it as a redirect URL or a webhook URL this is like webhook basically means\n\nA webhook is an HTTP request, triggered by an event in a source system(Facebook, Razorpay) and sent to\na destination system(like our app or any other startup).\n\n\nCan we Use Webhook  here -> No because who has the data our backend service our client is a webclient can't\nexpose a webhook but there is a usecase where webhookds can be helpful, when my client is not a webclient.\nWhen may be I am not Leetcode but I am somebody like spoj(Sphere online judge), So Spoj is like Leetcode as\nservice, whay spoj says that hey you want to make Leetcode dont put all of architecture in place I have all this\narchitecture in place already with me, you just register with me and send me your submissions that is coming from\nusers tell me where your testcases are and I will run it on my machine you just pay me,\n\nMight be it changed but for bigger ammount of time Codechef use Spoj.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
